reason.tex:
%text
By definition an invertible element $L(l, m) \in A$ is such that,
%
\begin{align}
  &(a, b)*(l, m) = (1, 0) = (l, m)*(a, b) \\
  \implies &(al, b+am)=(1, 0) \text{ and } (la, m+lb)=(1, 0) \\
  \implies &la=1, b+am=0, m+lb=0 \\
  \implies &l=\dfrac{1}{a},m=-\dfrac{b}{a}
\end{align}
